{
  "$schema": "https://docs.renovatebot.com/renovate-schema.json",
  "extends": [
    "config:recommended",
    "local>dryvist/.github",
  ],
  "nix": {
    "enabled": true,
  },
  "packageRules": [
    {
      "description": "Group MLX Python packages into a single PR",
      "matchManagers": ["pep621"],
      "matchFileNames": ["mlx-server/**"],
      "groupName": "mlx-packages",
    },
    {
      "description": "Group Orchestrator Python packages into a single PR",
      "matchManagers": ["pep621"],
      "matchFileNames": ["orchestrator/**"],
      "groupName": "orchestrator-packages",
    },
    {
      "description": [
        "Batch all custom-regex version pins in lib/versions.nix into ONE scheduled,",
        "auto-merged PR instead of one-PR-per-package. Renovate defaults to one PR per",
        "dependency; without this, low-priority custom-regex pins (huggingface-hub,",
        "browser-use, qwen-code, cclint, fabric, ...) each need their own branch/PR slot",
        "and lose the twice-weekly window race to lock-file maintenance, starving for",
        "weeks (huggingface-hub stuck at 1.15.0 from 2026-05 to 2026-07, which broke the",
        "hf CLI). The mlx trio is re-grouped into 'mlx-core' by the rule below (later",
        "packageRule wins on groupName), preserving its interlock and automerge:false.",
        "Schedule is inherited from the org preset's Mon/Thu custom.regex rule; majors",
        "are excluded so they still open individually under the 30-day major-default hold.",
      ],
      "matchManagers": ["custom.regex"],
      "matchFileNames": ["lib/versions.nix"],
      "matchUpdateTypes": ["minor", "patch"],
      "groupName": "nix tool version pins",
      "automerge": true,
    },
    {
      "description": [
        "Force the mlx core trio (mlx, mlx-lm, mlx-metal) to upgrade as a single PR",
        "regardless of which manager surfaced the bump (pep621 in mlx-server/, custom",
        "regex in lib/versions.nix). These packages have hard version interlocks:",
        "mlx-lm imports mlx, and mlx-metal ships in lockstep with mlx. A partial bump",
        "of one without the others can land us on an install-time-broken combination",
        "(e.g. mlx-lm 0.31.3 requires mlx>=0.31.2, so a mlx-lm-only bump fails).",
        "",
        "This groupName overrides the broader 'mlx-packages' rule above for these",
        "three specific packages (Renovate evaluates packageRules in order, later",
        "wins for overlapping options). vllm-mlx, parakeet-mlx, and mlx-vlm stay",
        "in 'mlx-packages' since they consume the trio rather than being part of it.",
        "",
        "Downfall to know about: Renovate's grouping only batches packages that all",
        "have an available update at the same time. If only mlx-lm has a new release",
        "in a given Renovate run, only mlx-lm will appear in the mlx-core PR — the",
        "group does NOT block partial bumps. The allowedVersions rules below are",
        "what actually guard against landing a half-upgraded broken combination.",
      ],
      "matchDatasources": ["pypi"],
      "matchPackageNames": ["mlx", "mlx-lm", "mlx-metal"],
      "groupName": "mlx-core",
      "groupSlug": "mlx-core",
    },
    {
      "description": [
        "Block the mlx 0.31.2 / 0.31.3 regression window for mlx and mlx-metal.",
        "See nix-ai#751 for full analysis. Short version: mlx 0.31.2 introduced",
        "thread-local stream semantics (upstream PR ml-explore/mlx#3281) that break",
        "vllm-mlx's scheduler thread — mlx-lm declares generation_stream at module",
        "import on the main thread, leaving the scheduler thread without a visible",
        "default stream. mlx-metal releases in lockstep with mlx and inherits the",
        "same regression. We rolled back to mlx 0.31.1 via PR #756.",
        "",
        "Why allowedVersions instead of minimumReleaseAge:",
        "A release-age delay only postpones the bump — after 30 days, Renovate",
        "would still propose 0.31.2 (it's been on PyPI for >30 days by then). The",
        "regression doesn't disappear with time, so a time-only filter is useless.",
        "Hard-blocking the broken version range is the only filter that actually",
        "keeps us off the bad versions while leaving newer releases auto-eligible.",
        "",
        "Why regex negation instead of '<0.31.2 || >=0.31.4':",
        "Renovate's pep440 versioning module documents '!/regex/' as the canonical",
        "syntax for excluding versions. Range OR with '||' is semver-specific and",
        "behavior with pep440 is undefined.",
        "",
        "Known downfalls:",
        "  1. We're betting upstream's fix ships as 0.31.4 or a different major/minor.",
        "     If they release 0.31.2.post1 or 0.31.3.post1 as the fix, this regex",
        "     allows it (the trailing $ anchors to exact version strings, so post-",
        "     releases slip through). That's intentional — post-releases are almost",
        "     always bugfix-only — but we'll still want to verify in the PR review.",
        "  2. If 0.31.4 ships and STILL has the regression, this rule won't catch it.",
        "     Treat the eventual auto-PR as a candidate fix, not a verified one:",
        "     run vllm-mlx end-to-end before merging.",
        "  3. Renovate's Dependency Dashboard issue surfaces blocked versions, so we",
        "     have passive visibility if upstream ships something weird.",
        "",
        "Removal tracking: nix-ai#762. Once we land on >=0.31.4 (or whatever post-",
        "regression version) and confirm vllm-mlx inference works, delete this rule.",
        "By that point '<0.31.2' is unreachable (we won't downgrade) and '>=0.31.4'",
        "is trivially satisfied, so the rule becomes inert documentation.",
      ],
      "matchDatasources": ["pypi"],
      "matchPackageNames": ["mlx", "mlx-metal"],
      "allowedVersions": "!/^0\\.31\\.[23]$/",
      "automerge": false,
    },
    {
      "description": [
        "Block mlx-lm 0.31.3. Same nix-ai#751 root cause: mlx-lm 0.31.3 raised its",
        "dependency floor to mlx>=0.31.2, dragging in the broken mlx version. The",
        "current pin from PR #756 is mlx-lm 0.31.2 (which predates the floor bump",
        "and works with mlx 0.31.1).",
        "",
        "This regex only blocks 0.31.3 specifically — 0.31.2 is the GOOD version",
        "for mlx-lm and must remain allowed (otherwise Renovate would flag the",
        "current pin as having no valid upgrade path and surface a noisy warning).",
        "",
        "Known downfalls (same shape as the mlx rule above):",
        "  1. A 0.31.3.post1 fix release would slip through this regex. Verify in",
        "     the eventual PR review before merging.",
        "  2. If 0.31.4 ships and still bundles a mlx>=0.31.2 floor that the mlx",
        "     rule above blocks, the mlx-core grouped PR will be inconsistent —",
        "     mlx-lm wants to bump but mlx can't. That asymmetry is the signal to",
        "     either widen the mlx allowedVersions or hold off on the mlx-lm bump.",
        "",
        "Removal tracking: nix-ai#762.",
      ],
      "matchDatasources": ["pypi"],
      "matchPackageNames": ["mlx-lm"],
      "allowedVersions": "!/^0\\.31\\.3$/",
      "automerge": false,
    },
  ],
}
